# Platform Coding Rules

## Intent
Set implementation standards for readability, modularity, and safe feature delivery across Next.js, React Native, and shared services.

## Mandatory
- Keep modules small and focused; one responsibility per component/service.
- Define typed contracts for API inputs/outputs and plugin command payloads.
- Validate all external input at boundaries (API, command bus, webhooks, queues).
- Use explicit error categories and structured error responses.
- Prefer configuration-driven behavior over hard-coded branching for plugin policies.

## Code Quality Rules
- Avoid hidden side effects in shared utilities.
- Avoid duplicate business logic across web/mobile; extract shared domain logic.
- Add migration-safe changes only; include backward compatibility behavior when needed.
- Ensure code files end with exactly one trailing newline (no missing newline, no extra blank lines at EOF).

## Prohibited
- Unbounded dynamic command execution.
- Direct secret access from client code.
- Silent catch-and-ignore error handling.